 spanischen Armada.  aThis volume contains dozens of articles written by Marx and Engels for the New York Tribune and the New American Cyclopedia. Seven texts have been edited here for the first time. Marx and Engels’ journalism focuses on the worldwide economic crisis of 1857–58, the Indian Rebellion, and European politics. Their work for the New American Cyclopedia includes biographical entries and articles on the military and a variety of other topics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aEconomics. 0aSocialism. 4aEngels, Friedrich. 4aMarx, Karl. 4aPublizistik. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aEngels.  aMarx.  ajournalism.1 aInternationale Marx-Engels-Stiftung, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2019z9783110606423oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMEGA 1975-2019z9783110688139oZDB-23-GKO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMEGA Prepaid 1975-2032z9783110691986oZDB-23-GKO0 cprintz978311051767540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311058598840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110585988423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110585988.jpg  a978-3-11-071956-7  DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DPHb2019  aZDB-23-GKOc1975d2019  aZDB-23-GKOc1975d2032